The paper proposes a novel probabilistic approach to multilevel clustering problems, which involves solving a joint optimization problem over spaces of probability measures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with probabilistic clustering and optimization problems, which are common topics in these fields. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves concepts related to information theory, data structures, and social networks.
